{"timestamp":"2026-07-18T13:29:07.592Z","type":"event_msg","payload":{"type":"agent_message","message":"Correct. I treated cold indexing as a legitimate benchmark condition; that was wrong for the intended agent workflow.\n\nThe harness starts its timer before launching Claude, then instructs Claude to invoke Entire Graph. It creates a fresh per-attempt cache, so the first Graph invocation builds the index **inside the measured task**. CBM is likewise instructed to index during the timed attempt.\n\nThe correct boundary is:\n\n1. Materialize the frozen checkout.\n2. Pre-index Entire Graph and CBM using their isolated caches.\n3. Verify the indexes correspond to the exact repository tree and product versions.\n4. Start Claude and the task timer.\n5. Measure only retrieval calls, reasoning, answer quality, tokens, and cost.\n6. Record indexing time separately as setup/maintenance—not agent-task latency.\n\nConsequences:\n\n- The reported **94.3s Entire Graph latency is invalid for comparison** with file tools.\n- My explanation that cold-start overhead was a natural disadvantage was incorrect. It is a harness defect.\n- Input/output token and Claude cost measurements remain mostly meaningful because local parsing itself consumes no model tokens, although pre-indexing could still change the agent’s behavior and therefore deserves a clean rerun.\n- The Zod relationship failure remains real; pre-indexing would not fix the incomplete result from the tested Graph head.\n- The current repaired head `0244ef1` has not received a correctly pre-indexed agentic run.\n\nAlso, prewarming must use the same Graph cache directory, tree, profile, and snapshot options as retrieval. A superficial warm-up with the wrong profile would still leave `neighbors` rebuilding its full snapshot.\n\nSo the smoke establishes useful quality diagnostics, but **it does not establish that file tools are faster than Entire Graph**. That latency conclusion should be withdrawn.","phase":"final_answer","memory_citation":null}}
{"timestamp":"2026-07-18T13:29:07.593Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"message","id":"msg_0bd6d73b974b1fab016a5b7fa3909481918f3e2dff8f6fd95c","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"output_text","text":"Correct. I treated cold indexing as a legitimate benchmark condition; that was wrong for the intended agent workflow.\n\nThe harness starts its timer before launching Claude, then instructs Claude to invoke Entire Graph. It creates a fresh per-attempt cache, so the first Graph invocation builds the index **inside the measured task**. CBM is likewise instructed to index during the timed attempt.\n\nThe correct boundary is:\n\n1. Materialize the frozen checkout.\n2. Pre-index Entire Graph and CBM using their isolated caches.\n3. Verify the indexes correspond to the exact repository tree and product versions.\n4. Start Claude and the task timer.\n5. Measure only retrieval calls, reasoning, answer quality, tokens, and cost.\n6. Record indexing time separately as setup/maintenance—not agent-task latency.\n\nConsequences:\n\n- The reported **94.3s Entire Graph latency is invalid for comparison** with file tools.\n- My explanation that cold-start overhead was a natural disadvantage was incorrect. It is a harness defect.\n- Input/output token and Claude cost measurements remain mostly meaningful because local parsing itself consumes no model tokens, although pre-indexing could still change the agent’s behavior and therefore deserves a clean rerun.\n- The Zod relationship failure remains real; pre-indexing would not fix the incomplete result from the tested Graph head.\n- The current repaired head `0244ef1` has not received a correctly pre-indexed agentic run.\n\nAlso, prewarming must use the same Graph cache directory, tree, profile, and snapshot options as retrieval. A superficial warm-up with the wrong profile would still leave `neighbors` rebuilding its full snapshot.\n\nSo the smoke establishes useful quality diagnostics, but **it does not establish that file tools are faster than Entire Graph**. That latency conclusion should be withdrawn."}],"phase":"final_answer","internal_chat_message_metadata_passthrough":{"turn_id":"019f7569-6161-7702-9ed1-5f5d3ff8fdff"}}}
